*BS:* I think these things are almost always much more macro than people wa=
nt to believe, and I think the macro conditions for us are very, very favor=
able. I think the urgency that the Department [of Defense] feels around eve=
rything happening with respect to China, the threat there, Taiwan, I think =
the war in Ukraine, all the lessons there, how the international partners a=
re all viewing this, and their need to rearm and increase their defense spe=
nding, and then obviously you have all the changes coming in with Trump, th=
e influence of Elon, all of those pieces I think have massively shifted the=
 view to what defense is going to be in the future, and how do we have to s=
pend and build correctly for the right technologies, the right capabilities=
, and actually take advantage of all everything happening in Silicon Valley=
, that otherwise was just not making it in.

*When we talked last time, you put forward the thesis, and I think this is =
an overall theme of Anduril, that you need to build the defense company of =
the future, because the DoD doesn=E2=80=99t get it. That=E2=80=99s why you =
need to go start with venture, and when they wake up, you=E2=80=99ll be the=
re waiting. I think you could certainly make the thesis that that has worke=
