un low-cost bombers or autonomous underwater vehicles, there=E2=80=99s all =
these ways to get things into the fight that are more expensive, but then I=
=E2=80=99m deploying a lot of cheaper things with it. So there=E2=80=99s a =
lot of ways can think creatively about this.

But in a certain sense, the Department has landed it into this one narrow l=
ocal optima, and they=E2=80=99re maxing that out and they=E2=80=99re like, =
=E2=80=9COh, everything=E2=80=99s expensive, so it has to get more expensiv=
e=E2=80=9D, and then they kind of end in this death spiral. But there=E2=80=
=99s this alternative, which could be very cheap and very scaled that you c=
an get to and our view is we=E2=80=99re building all the requisite things t=
o get there, finding ways to get them inserted because it will enable a who=
le new class of weapons, platforms and all these things, and a new concept =
of war-fighting, but it is going to take time because the whole system has =
been optimized around a totally different equilibrium.

